From: Daniel Milisic <dmilisic@desktopecho.com>
Date: Fri, 3 Apr 2026 18:00:00 -0300
Subject: [PATCH] Remove unused global grpc ClientContext

The pinned netsim revision already uses per-stream ClientContext instances,
but it still leaves behind an unused namespace-scope ClientContext object.
On this aarch64 Fedora build, netsimd is crashing in the corresponding
global constructor before normal daemon startup.

Drop the stale global so netsimd no longer needs to run grpc::ClientContext
construction during static initialization.
---
 src/backend/grpc_client.cc | 1 -
 1 file changed, 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/src/backend/grpc_client.cc b/src/backend/grpc_client.cc
index ff43e8f2..6031585b 100644
--- a/src/backend/grpc_client.cc
+++ b/src/backend/grpc_client.cc
@@ -52,7 +52,6 @@ std::unordered_map<uint32_t, grpc::ClientContext> contexts_;
 // Single connection to a server with multiple StreamPackets calls
 std::string server_;
 std::shared_ptr<grpc::Channel> channel_;
-grpc::ClientContext context_;
 std::unique_ptr<netsim::packet::PacketStreamer::Stub> stub_;
 
 // Call the StreamPackets RPC on server.
-- 
2.49.0

